<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0da48d9b-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21123"><num value="21123">§ 21123.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to any funds authorized to be appropriated to the Commission under <ref href="/us/usc/t52/s20930">section 20930 of this title</ref>, there are authorized to be appropriated to carry out this subchapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0da48d9c-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21123/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> $5,000,000 for fiscal year 2003; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0da48d9d-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0" identifier="/us/usc/t52/s21123/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> such sums as may be necessary for each succeeding fiscal year.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id0da48d9e-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/252/tV/s503">Pub. L. 107–252, title V, § 503</ref>, <date date="2002-10-29">Oct. 29, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1717">116 Stat. 1717</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0da48d9f-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id0da48da0-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id0da48da1-2931-11f1-afae-ea39e71ac6b0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s15523">section 15523 of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
